// Two infinite loops with cross-edges that break into each other: L1 = {1, 2}, L2 = {3, 4},
// with 2 -> 3 (L1 can jump into L2's body) and 4 -> 1 (L2 can jump back into L1's body).
// Mutual reachability collapses everything into one terminal SCC {1,2,3,4}, so
// `add_infinite_loop_post_dominators` adds a single impossible edge return_ -> 4 (highest-rank
// input node in the SCC) and post-domination is total over the input.
//
//       0
//      / \
//   ->1   3<-
//   |  \ /  |
//   |   X   |
//   |  / \  |
//    -2   4-
//      \_/
//   (2 -> 3, 4 -> 1 are the cross-edges)

cond,0,1,3
code,1,2
cond,2,1,3
code,3,4
cond,4,3,1
